    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>Sketch the graph of the function <m>y = {{f}}(x)</m> 
            on the period <m>[0,2\pi]</m>. On your graph, indicate the points
            at each of the <m>x</m>-values: 
            <m mode="display">
            0, 
            \frac{\pi}{2}, 
            \pi, 
            \frac{3\pi}{2}, 
            2\pi
            </m>
            </p>

        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p>
                <image
                    source = "assets/TRIG3/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show1.png"
                    description = "a graph of one period of $y = {{f}}(x)$"
                />
            </p>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>Consider the function <m>g(x) = {{A}} {{f}}( {{arg}} ) </m>.</p>
                <list>
                    <item><p>What is the amplitude of <m>g</m>?</p></item>
                    <item><p>What is the period of <m>g</m>?</p></item>
                    <item><p>Sketch the graph of <m>y=g(x)</m> on one period. 
                    On your graph, indicate the <m>x</m>-values at which 
                    <m>g</m> has maxima, minima, and zeroes.</p></item>
                </list>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
                <item><p>The amplitude of <m>g</m> is <m>{{amp}}</m>.</p></item>
                <item><p>the period of <m>g</m> is <m>{{T}}</m>.</p></item>
                <item><p>
                    <image
                        source = "assets/TRIG3/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show2.png"
                        description = "a graph of one period of $y = {{g(x)}}$"
                    /></p></item>
